---
/**
 * Redesigned Stages Section (formerly Three Pillars)
 */
---

<section class="stages section-pad">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="stages-eyebrow reveal">The Process</p>
        <h2 class="reveal">
            With regularity and repetition, the body naturally begins to:
        </h2>
        <div class="stages-grid">
            <div class="stage-card reveal">
                <p class="stage-number">One</p>
                <h3>Release</h3>
                <p>
                    This is where the overwhelm begins to dissolve and the edge
                    begins to soften. Stress leaves the body naturally, the mind
                    settles and you experience deep rest. Often for the first
                    time in years.
                </p>
                <p class="stage-feel">
                    Feel spacious again — mentally, emotionally, physically.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-card reveal">
                <p class="stage-number">Two</p>
                <h3>Restore</h3>
                <p>
                    With the load lifted, a natural steadiness begins to show
                    up. Letting go and slowing down become routine. The noise
                    quiets, your energy returns and you begin responding to life
                    differently. More naturally. More creatively. More
                    consciously.
                </p>
                <p class="stage-feel">
                    Feel clearer, more grounded, more present in your own life.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-card reveal">
                <p class="stage-number">Three</p>
                <h3>Remember</h3>
                <p>
                    Be reminded of what you are — body, mind and soul — realise
                    your true nature. Your true essence. Experience more joy,
                    more ease, more time for what matters. Establish a sense of
                    being and happiness within yourself.
                </p>
                <p class="stage-feel">
                    Feel supported, lighter, and genuinely excited about the
                    future.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="stage-footnote reveal">
            You don't have to try. The technique does the work for you.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    .stages {
        background: var(--color-warm-white);
    }
    .stages-eyebrow {
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 4px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--color-eucalyptus);
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .stages h2 {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 36px);
        font-style: italic;
        margin-bottom: 80px;
        color: var(--color-indigo);
    }
    .stages-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 60px;
    }
    .stage-card {
        padding: 48px 32px;
        background: white;
        border-top: 2px solid var(--color-sea-green);
        transition: transform 0.4s ease, box-shadow 0.4s ease;
    }
    .stage-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-4px);
        box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(31, 47, 58, 0.08);
    }
    .stage-number {
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--color-eucalyptus);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .stage-card h3 {
        font-size: 26px;
        font-style: italic;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        color: var(--color-indigo);
    }
    .stage-card p {
        font-size: 16px;
        color: var(--color-slate);
        line-height: 1.85;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .stage-card .stage-feel {
        font-style: italic;
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        color: var(--color-sea-green);
        font-size: 15px;
        margin-top: 24px;
        padding-top: 24px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-mist);
    }
    .stage-footnote {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 64px;
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 20px;
        color: var(--color-slate);
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .stages-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            gap: 32px;
        }
    }
</style>
